##const/4 v0, 0x0__Toast.LENGTH_SHORT
#The constant Toast.LENGTH_SHORT in Android represents the duration for which a toast message is displayed for a short time, which is about 2 seconds (2000 milliseconds).

Details:
It is an integer constant with the value 0.
Internally, this corresponds roughly to a 2-second display time for the toast message.
The other option is Toast.LENGTH_LONG, which is about 3.5 seconds (3500 milliseconds) duration.

##In smali or Java, using const/4 v0, 0x0 or Toast.LENGTH_SHORT indicates that the toast should appear briefly around 2 seconds before disappearing automatically.
